      "sha256": "57c8a2ed36fb6f5430fe65254adb753dbe1e2247d8f99ad2aecdac4daa0d9e45",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A problem of Komj\\'{a}th. The existence of such a $2$-colouring is sometimes known as Property B."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "6f7dedd679e0296b95f696f049806059c1fcdffc5060f9883a46f1ff6883d8ec",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $(A_i)$ be a family of sets with $\\lvert A_i\\rvert=\\aleph_0$ for all $i$, such that for any $i\\neq j$ we have $\\lvert A_i\\cap A_j\\rvert$ finite and $\\neq 1$. Is there a $2$-colouring of $\\cup A_i$ such that no $A_i$ is monochromatic?"
    }
  },
